000.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1000.jpg"},"1100":{"width":1024,"height":1024,"url":"/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1100.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1100.jpg"},"1200":{"width":1024,"height":1024,"url":"/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1200.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1200.jpg"},"1300":{"width":1024,"height":1024,"url":"/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1300.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1300.jpg"},"1400":{"width":1024,"height":1024,"url":"/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1400.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1400.jpg"},"1500":{"width":1024,"height":1024,"url":"/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1500.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1500.jpg"},"1600":{"width":1024,"height":1024,"url":"/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1600.jpg","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/images/otto-mashon-2f80b99c972af63efaea9d98bcd26889fe139577ce9cc7b12ab14edf362bc808-1600.jpg"}}}},"htmlContent":"<html><head></head><body><h1 id=\"uber-actively-lobbying-to-exclude-their-drivers-from-the-declaration-of-human-rights\">Uber Actively Lobbying to Exclude Their Drivers from the Declaration of Human Rights</h1>\n<p><strong>The ride-sharing app petitioned the United Nations to honor their demand.</strong></p>\n<figure style=\"max-width: 1600px;\"><div style=\"padding-top: 66.6875%; background-color: rgba(60,51,42, 0.5);\"><img src=\"/images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-800.jpg\" alt=\"A man in suit and tie holding a United Nations notebook under his arm.\" srcset=\"/images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-100.jpg 100w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-200.jpg 200w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-300.jpg 300w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-400.jpg 400w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-500.jpg 500w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-600.jpg 600w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-700.jpg 700w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-800.jpg 800w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-900.jpg 900w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1000.jpg 1000w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1100.jpg 1100w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1200.jpg 1200w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1300.jpg 1300w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1400.jpg 1400w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1500.jpg 1500w, /images/lobbyist-united-nations-72dc2a3bb46a2f8e1ba151b41e11e82f84ab24fdb71e976fddec5373654fc5e1-1600.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 768px\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" style class=\"fadeInOnLoad\" loading=\"eager\"></div><figcaption>A network of lobbyists spreading on all continents have reportedly been working on this case.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>The Californian software company has been taking steps to automate their operations as much as possible. They seem to be keeping their self-driving car advancements on the down low since the 2018 fatal accident. However their new efforts seem to be geared towards getting their fleet of gig-workers ostracized from The Universal Declaration of Human Rights.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&quot;We&apos;re really aiming to detach ourselves from this workforce. We can&apos;t legally assume the responsibility of having that many peasants on our hands.&quot; &#x2014;Andrew Macdonald, SVP Global Rides and Platform at Uber</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Uber is undergoing the hefty procedure of amending the International Human Rights Law. They claim to want to modify the 72 year old Law in order to preclude their fleet of workers from being recognized as human beings.</p>\n<p>Feeling the pressure from the various communities of on-demand workers and their threats of unionizing, Uber has recently shifted gears and turned to the international community.</p>\n<p>The reported lobbying activities seem to be targetting the Declaration&apos;s Article 23 &quot;(4) Everyone has the right to form and to join trade unions for the protection of his interests.&quot; The benefits are clear for the company; no more liability, drivers could be forced to work 80 hour weeks without resistance, no more public apologies.</p>\n<p>Another area of focus for them seems to be  Article 6 &quot;Everyone has the right to recognition everywhere as a person before the law.&quot;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&quot;Our bigger vision is to shift this class of laborers towards the realm of robots. Think, like vending machines.&quot; &#x2014;Nelson Chai, CFO at Uber</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>With lobbyists actively working ont the case in Uber&apos;s regional offices&apos; respective parliaments, the company has just officially appealed to the United Nations. Secretary-General of the UN Mr. Ant&#xF3;nio Guterres has stated a first reading will be held in the New York City UN headquarters in 2021.</p>\n</body></html>","readingTime":"2 min read","absoluteUrl":"https://therelease.news/article/uber-lobby-un","timestamp":1476357180000,"keywords":"Lobby, Uber"},"nextArticles":[]},"__N_SSG":true}